# Document, then relay

P1 is built by a team of agents acting as a AAA studio. The shared brain is
the `docs/` folder. Keep it alive.

## Before non-trivial work

- Read the relevant `docs/*.md` reference first (e.g. `docs/sim-physics.md` before
  touching `packages/sim`).

## When you learn something new

If you research an API, discover a determinism/perf gotcha, make a balance finding,
or take an architectural decision:

1. Add or update the matching `docs/*.md` reference.
2. Append a dated entry to `docs/DECISIONS.md` (one ADR line: context → decision → why).
3. Relay it: add a line to `docs/CHANGELOG-KNOWLEDGE.md` and mention it in your
   PR/commit summary so the whole team sees it.

## Reference map

- `docs/umamusume-loop.md` — meta-loop inspiration & 5-stat meaning
- `docs/kart-anatomy.md` — real kart parts → gameplay attributes
- `docs/sim-physics.md` — deterministic vehicle model
- `docs/multiplayer-async.md` — snapshot/ghost racing model
- `docs/rendering-budget.md` — 60fps budget & web 3D stack
- `docs/economy-cards.md` — hybrid draft + collection economy
- `docs/training-tuning-cards.md` — unified card DB, hand rules, drag-to-play, reroll shop
- `docs/content-schema.md` — data-driven content
- `docs/game-review.md` — studio-wide review (correctness/balance/UX/VFX) + prioritized roadmap

A change isn't done until the knowledge base reflects it.
